<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-14T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-14T21:00:00-05:00" n="1026" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1026">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5034 Registration/3–1446: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Embassy in China</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-14T21:00:00-05:00">March 14,
                                1946—9 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>469. American business interests are in quandary as to what is present status
                        of revised company law, and whether registration is required prior to March
                        31, and if so under what law. Dr. Robert Huang, attorney for China-America
                        Council is of opinion, as is Chinese Embassy, he reports, that registration
                        requirement prior to March 31 is under “Regulations for Registration of
                        Companies,” June 9, 1943. Commerce requests clarification.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>